<title>Lateinische Synonyme und Etymologien</title>
                <note>
<p>IN VAIN</p>
<p>frustra refers to something being in vain in the sense that the agent's purposes were frustrated.</p>
<p>nequidquam refers to something being to no purpose and coming to nothing.</p>
<p>incassum refers to something coming to nothing because of a fault on the part of the agent.</p>
                </note>
